FBIS4-40474 "drsov117_d_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-117 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 Regional Affairs Chechnya Asks for Flight Resumption Chechnya Asks for Flight Resumption LD1606195294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1833 GMT 16 Jun 94 LD1606195294 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] The Chechen Foreign Ministry called on the Russian Transportation Ministry to resume flights from Moscow to Groznyy that were suspended ostensibly for security considerations. The ministry's letter emphasized that the situation was quiet in Groznyy. The Chechen Foreign Ministry described the unilateral suspension of flights by Moscow as a violation of international law which does serious harm to bilateral relations.
